"""You can see the description of the task using the code specified in the title on leetcode.
This program has O(1) complexity by time and O(1) by space.

I generally don't like problems like this. 
Even though it's not difficult, it requires thinking in terms of probability theory, 
and I'm not a big fan of cramming everything "technical" into a single box.

After playing around with test cases, it’s immediately clear that the answer is 0.5, but what is the underlying mathematics?

proof  https://leetcode.com/problems/airplane-seat-assignment-probability/solutions/411905/its-not-obvious-to-me-at-all-foolproof-e-efj2/
"""

class Solution:
    def nthPersonGetsNthSeat(self, n: int) -> float:
        return 1 / 2 if n > 1 else 1.0
